				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><em>Haunted: Halloween '85</em> for NES does something similar with its sprite CHR. It emulates a sprite system with 256 16x16 CHRs, uploading two per frame to one of two buffers allocated to each entity and switching to the next animation frame only once all needed 16x16s are in place. On Super NES, it should be easier, as you don't need two buffers if no single cel needs more than 5K.<br /><br />But you still need someone to draw plausible sprite cels with which to test a sprite system including this sort of OBJ-ExGrafix simulator, so that you don't end up over-relying on peculiarities of your synthetic test tiles.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

