				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I thought more about this idea, and I thought that it might be easier to do 16x16 sprites in groups of 2, for a lot of reasons:<br /><br />-half of the SNES's memory space can be used for sprites.<br />-32x32 and 16x16 sprites would have the same alignment.<br />-All sprite pairs have a page aligned address.<br />-DMA routine can be made more efficient.  Possibly around 5kB at once without bars.<br /><br />The downsides are slightly less flexible 16x16 sprites, and doing 48x48 rotating sprites would have a much more confusing mapping.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
